##Wang Zhenyao: epidemic unprecedented, the need to coordinate the response across departments, but also to avoid duplication

I-CAIJING

Sudden disasters are changing, from traditional single disasters, to more complex, more cross-border; emergency management has also changed, the traditional division of professional management, single-handed encountered no small setback

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
CAIJING reporter, Li Xinyin intern, Ma Wenbin

Editor | Shi Zhiliang

New Crown Pneumonia, a sudden public event, gradually evolved into a multi-faceted economic and social mixed, cross-border disaster, which has aroused the attention and hot debate of disaster relief workers.

"after more than a decade of disaster relief at the Ministry of Civil Affairs, I have never encountered a disaster of this complexity and scale, " Wang Zhenyao, president of the Beijing Normal University, said in a telephone interview with Caijing, the epidemic situation of NCP combined the characteristics of the three disasters of SARS in 2003, the southern freezing in 2008 and the Wenchuan County earthquake.

Wang Zhenyao was previously director of the Department of Disaster Relief and Relief and the Department of Social Welfare and Charity Promotion of the Ministry of Civil Affairs. During the SARS and Wenchuan County earthquakes, he was involved in the dispatch of materials. In the field of disaster relief, a four-level National Response System for natural disaster relief has been established, speeding up the standardization process of disaster relief work.

"It looks like everyone is starting to get back to work gradually. " Wang Zhenyao has been keeping track of the development of the epidemic. When he spoke to a reporter from Caijing, he said that there were more cars on the road at night, and that the east third ring road was blocked again, driving intermittently for an hour.

Wang Zhenyao believes that the scale of the epidemic is too large, objectively has evolved into a catastrophe. However, the existing Public Health Emergency Response Mechanism and emergency management system plans are still to be improved. There must be a standardized set of response plans that clearly identify the responsibility to the person.

"disaster relief must be concrete. In Times of crisis, we can not go around discussing and voting. We must make decisions and assume responsibility by those directly responsible on the front line. We can not let everyone have the final say and report everywhere, but we should not assume responsibility. This is a valuable experience that needs to be taken seriously", wang Zhenyao said bluntly.

Wang Zhenyao, who has been fighting against natural disasters for more than 10 years, calls for the establishment of an emergency management committee at the top level, through which the permanent body coordinates the various functional departments and accumulates experience in handling emergency affairs, drawing on the Coordination Mechanism of a large ministry system and a large committee, can effectively play the dual advantages.

Wang suggested that the government should share information with social groups and encourage them to act in accordance with the law and their functions. In Wenchuan County's experience, the dynamism of social organisation can make up for the weakness of government.

If the plan is not perfect, we will be passive in the face of disaster

CAIJING: You have dealt with many major disasters during your tenure. How is this new pneumonia epidemic different from the past?

Wang Zhenyao: This is a catastrophe that mankind faces in modern society, and it is impossible to deal with it with fully mature experience. In more than a decade of work, the Ministry of Civil Affairs has never encountered such a complex and large-scale epidemic disaster. It was a huge Black Swan, came quietly, had to close the city, this is a very large public health emergency.

I experienced SARS in 2003, and was directly involved in the handling of major disasters such as the freezing rain and snow disaster in southern China in early 2008, and the earthquake disaster relief in Wenchuan County. But this epidemic included infectious diseases, the Spring Festival period, and many factors affecting tens of millions of people, the degree of complexity is more complicated and larger than the three disasters mentioned above.

This time there was a plague in the midst of the plague. With the expansion of the epidemic, the late involved in the residents'daily necessities of logistics supply and all kinds of personnel relief and security, which is similar to a major disaster, epidemic and disaster began to shift.

CAIJING: When the disaster and epidemic situation back and forth, the existing mechanism to deal with it? Why will there be structural shortage of goods and materials in front of the poor operation of the situation?

Wang Zhenyao: At present, China's public health emergency response and even emergency management system planning mechanism still needs to be improved. When the provinces launch a first-level response to public health emergencies, while carrying out epidemic prevention and Rescue, road closure and suspension of markets, in many aspects, such as medical supply, distribution of daily necessities, replacement of ambulance personnel, prevention of fund chain breaking during the delay of returning to work, coordination and coordination of volunteers, etc. . At present, there is still a lack of multiple intensity of the comprehensive plan to deal with the small probability of a major emergency.

When I was the director of the Disaster Relief Department of the Ministry of Civil Affairs, My responsibility was to ensure the livelihood of the people and the basic livelihood of the frontline emergency (including medical) staff. The men and horses did not move, but the grain and grass went first. The guarantee of relief materials is one of the focuses of the relief work. I have always stressed that the disaster areas must establish a list of relief materials system. At present, the previous stage, we do not know the development of the epidemic, coupled with inadequate preparation for the response plan, in the face of disaster or some passive.

The evolution of disasters is more complex, and the system construction is in the right time

"CAIJING" : The disasters in the new century generally have a cross-border nature, natural disasters, public health emergencies, public safety emergencies, accidents of production safety responsibility and so on are often easy to interact with each other, but how can cross-sectoral assistance in complex disasters be achieved?

Wang Zhenyao: based on my experience in dealing with natural disasters for more than 10 years, it is particularly important to have a coordination mechanism at the national level. With the help of this mechanism and detailed plans, synergy can be formed and the difficulties in disaster relief and prevention can be easily solved. The outbreak involves the public health profession and requires more detailed and specific normative national action programmes.

CAIJING: In 2018, the Emergency Management Department came into being, but its powers and responsibilities do not include dealing with public health emergencies, which makes it difficult for the epidemic to play its professional advantage. What do you think of this?

Wang Zhenyao: This epidemic started a public health event, did not start the natural disaster emergency response plan, which is understandable. However, this has made it difficult for the Department of Emergency Management to initiate institutional support in accordance with the plan, drawing on its extensive experience in dealing with natural disasters, unless specifically requested.

That is why the functions of the Disaster Relief Division of the Ministry of Civil Affairs have been transferred to the Emergency Management Department. However, the Ministry of Emergency Management can not respond in accordance with the Disaster Emergency Plan. Since the Ministry of Civil Affairs assumes the responsibility of major disaster donation, it can only be stipulated by the Red Cross, Charity Federation and other organizations to coordinate donations. From the current development, although this epidemic is no less than any of the major disasters, but there is an emergency management departments can not start disaster emergency preparedness embarrassing situation.

CAIJING: In 2005, after the SARS epidemic ended, the State Council General Office had set up an emergency management office, responsible for coordinating the coordination of multiple ministries to deal with emergencies.

Wang Zhenyao: At that time, the Emergency Management Office of the State Council provided a coordinating body for cross-border emergency response of various ministries and departments. Each department was able to submit information here for unified processing for decision-making by the leadership. At that time, not only was all the information visually visible, but coordination meetings were frequently attended and the directors of the divisions and branches with responsibility for the major emergency response systems were familiar. After the reform of the ministry system, each ministry reverts to the traditional system of division of labor and reports directly to the head of the department, which results in the lack of the ability to collect and analyze the information in the previous paragraph and may weaken the authority of the local authority to deal with the epidemic situation.

CAIJING: After a period of time after the disaster, now that the temporary headquarters have been set up at the top, the coordination has been much smoother. Is it necessary to fix this system?

Wang Zhenyao: This system should be further standardized and fixed. From a global perspective, emergency management reform is a huge challenge for all countries. There also appears to be a need for an integrated coordination mechanism within the State Department, a permanent body through which all parties can gain experience in dealing with emergencies with skill. With the help of the coordination mechanism of the big department system and the big committee, the double advantages can be brought into play effectively.

The responsibility for disaster relief should be clear and accepted by the people

CAIJING: What was the most impressive thing about the rescue of the Wenchuan County earthquake in 2008?

Wang Zhenyao: the State's Emergency Plan must have the power and responsibility to the person, clear the function, and elaborate the mechanism of starting the plan. For example, in the four-tier Natural Disaster Response Mechanism, the National Disaster Reduction Committee is composed of 34 ministries and commissions under the leadership of the vice-premier of the State Council, including the relevant heads of the armed forces, from the director of the Disaster Relief Department of the Ministry of Civil Affairs, the vice-minister and the minister to the vice-premier of the State Council, the Response Mechanism shall be activated according to the level of the disaster. Once a disaster has occurred and the response level has been reached, the corresponding central working group must reach the disaster area within 24 hours and make initial arrangements for the lives of the victims within 24 hours.

If there is no standardized processing mechanism, this is not easy. In the emergency response system of each kind of natural disaster, there are a series of clear responsibility index. I fear that I forget, specifically in the office behind the hanging of the response standards and procedures of the large chart, every day to see, until memorized.

Disaster relief must remember to prevaricate, who is responsible for the response, this can not be counted lost. Disaster Relief must be specific. In time of emergency, we can not consult, discuss and vote everywhere. We must assume the responsibility of those responsible for the disaster. We can not let everyone have the final say and report everywhere. This is a valuable lesson that needs to be taken seriously.

CAIJING: The self-rescue and mutual rescue of non-governmental forces have aroused people's concern, but there have also been cases of blind action and "no way to serve the country" . Is it necessary to set up a special interface in order to fully mobilize society in case of disaster?

Wang Zhenyao: in the face of major disasters, the government should communicate with social organizations and encourage them to act according to law and function. Volunteers and charities should be encouraged to play a role, even in the event of an epidemic, they are not absent, doing a good job, moving people, and some volunteers have given their precious lives. Han Hong's donation was disputed, but he was the first to rush in, giving everyone confidence!

The vitality of the social organization can make up for the deficiency of the government. In the case of Wenchuan County, where many government workers were killed, civil society played a big role. In the face of the epidemic, volunteers need professional training, more need government support. I think the Red Cross has a platform role to play on both sides of the aisle, and it's a shame that he was marginalised when he was scheduled to receive a donation.

"CAIJING" : from the international experience, this kind of disaster have other mountains of stone?

Wang Zhenyao: It is necessary to learn from foreign experience, but it is not necessarily feasible to copy experience. In 2008, when I was rotating chairman of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation's Disaster Relief Committee, many countries wanted China to give them in-house training after Peru introduced Wenchuan County's rescue experience.

Australian disaster officials told me at the time that the Chinese experience would help improve the Australian system. After the March 11 earthquake in Japan, I went to the scene to evaluate the rescue and found that, after learning from Japan, we are constantly enriched and sound, and now people want to learn from us.

I personally recommend to study overseas for emergency management relatively sound training system, including the establishment of public health emergency response, Natural Disaster Emergency Response Related Professional, the Central Party School (the State Administration College) will be strengthened in its emergency training courses, and disaster reduction training will be widely carried out in primary and secondary schools and even kindergartens, so as to better disseminate relevant knowledge and enhance the ability of national civil epidemic prevention and disaster prevention and emergency relief.
